page.title: 01KEELBY GAZETEER
page.content: Keelby Village is situated in North Lincolnshire.It is to the northwest of Grimsby, & to the south of Scunthorpe. It has a population of approximately{ {2500}, about a quarter of which are under 16.It contains about{870}houses. It is mainly a{farming}community, and is surrounded by fields. It's main crops are{wheat},{corn}&{rape}.Some of the houses are quite new, while some others are old.The main constrution material is{brick}while a few of the older houses are stone. It contains a Norman{Church}and a brick built{chapel}.It has a small Post Office, foodstore, newsagents, winebar and D.I.Y. store. Keelby lies at the foot of the Lincolnshire{Wolds}which run down the the south of the county.
